# Projects

## 🔹 1. RFID-based Traffic Control System
A smart traffic control system that adjusts lane priority using IR sensors and detects stolen vehicles in real time using RFID.

**Features**
- IR-based traffic density sensing  
- Automatic lane priority  
- RFID stolen vehicle detection  
- I2C LCD live status display  
- Servo motor gate control  

**Tech Used:** Arduino, IR Sensor, RFID-RC522, Servo Motor, I2C LCD  


---

## 🔹 2. Color Sorting Conveyor System
A dual-servo based color sorting system that categorizes objects based on color.

**Features**
- One servo drops items one-by-one  
- Second servo sorts based on detected color  
- Real-time processing  

**Tech Used:** Arduino, Color Sensor, Servo Motors  


---

## 🔹 3. Gesture-Based Switch Control (Medical Use)
A touchless switching system for patients with limited mobility.  
Controls electrical appliances using simple hand gestures.

**Features**
- No physical contact  
- Safe for medical environment  
- Gesture-to-relay control  

**Tech Used:** Arduino / ESP32, Gesture Sensor, Relay Module  


---

## 🔹 4. Simple IoT Monitoring Prototype (Mini Project)
A small IoT system that monitors sensor data and sends updates through Wi-Fi.

**Tech Used:** ESP32, MQTT / Wi-Fi
